               <p>GEORGE CHIVES. I am a <rs id="t18270405-254-viclabel1397" type="occupation">carman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-254-victim1428 t18270405-254-viclabel1397"></join>. On the 27th of March I was driving my waggon in <placeName id="t18270405-254-crimeloc1398">Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270405-254-crimeloc1398" type="placeName" value="Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270405-254-crimeloc1398" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270405-254-off1395 t18270405-254-crimeloc1398"></join> - I had a coat in it, and missed it about nine o'clock - it was produced to me afterwards by an officer - it is here.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270405-254-person1429">
                  GEORGE 
                  HASLEWOOD WORRALL
               <interp inst="t18270405-254-person1429" type="surname" value="HASLEWOOD WORRALL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-254-person1429" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270405-254-person1429" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was sent for from the Compter to take charge of the prisoner and this coat, about a quarter-past nine o'clock; a person came afterwards, who said he saw him take it out of the waggon - he is not here - the prisoner was present, and said he did it through distress - when he got to Guildhall, he said he was in a place and received 18s. a week.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The coat was lying on the ground in the mud, and I picked it up.</p>
               <p>G. CHIVES re-examined. It could not have fallen out, but it might have been pulled out.</p>
